Chocolate Cookies

Ingredients:
Butter, 8 tbs
Sugar, ⅔ Cup
Vanilla extract, 1 tsp
Egg, 1
Flour, 1 Cup
Baking soda, 1 tsp
Salt, 1 pinch
Unsweetened cocoa powder, ⅓ Cup
Semi-sweet chocolate chips, 1 Cup
Cinnamon, 1 pinch
Cayanne pepper, 1 pinch

Equipment:
Baking sheet
Mixing bowl x2
Electric beater
Whisk


Line baking sheet with parchment paper. Cream butter and sugar in one bowl. Mix egg & vanilla into butter. In other bowl, whisk flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cayanne, & cocoa powder together. Beat dry ingredients into wet. Fold in chocolate chips. Spoon onto baking sheet. Bake at 350°F for 8-9 minutes. Let cool and serve warm.
